		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "of user generated sentiment data ( e.g. , reviews , blogs ) . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Due to the mismatch among different domains , ",
			"relation": "cause"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "a sentiment classifier ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "trained in one domain ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "may not work well ",
			"relation": "same-unit"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "when directly applied to other domains . <S>",
			"relation": "condition"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Thus , domain adaptation for sentiment classification algorithms are highly desirable to reduce the domain discrepancy and manual labeling costs . <S>",
			"relation": "result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "To address the above challenge , ",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "we propose a novel domain adaptation method , ",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "called Bi-Transferring Deep Neural Networks ( BTDNNs ) . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "The proposed BTDNNs attempts to transfer the source domain examples to the target domain , ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "and also transfer the target domain examples to the source domain . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "The linear transformation of BTDNNs ensures the feasibility of transferring between domains , ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "and the distribution consistency between the transferred domain and the desirable domain is constrained with a linear data reconstruction manner . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "As a result , the transferred source domain is supervised ",
			"relation": "result"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
			"parent": 17,
			"text": "and follows similar distribution as the target domain . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 19,
			"parent": 17,
			"text": "Therefore , any supervised method can be used on the transferred source domain ",
			"relation": "result"
		},
		{
			"id": 20,
			"parent": 19,
			"text": "to train a classifier for sentiment classification in a target domain . <S>",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 21,
			"parent": 24,
			"text": "We conduct experiments on a benchmark ",
			"relation": "progression"
		},
		{
			"id": 22,
